HEADWORD: peachwood
<hw>peach"wood`</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧ch"w⟦oocr⟧d`)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A tropical tree <spn>Caesalpinia echinata</spn>, having
a prickly trunk; its heavy red wood yields a red dye and is used for
cabinetry.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Caesalpinia echinata.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The heavy red wood of the <spn>Caesalpinia
echinata</spn>; brazilwood; pernambuco wood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peachy</ent>⟦br⟧
